div.p:
On this coaſt, and on the rock Hiſkyr, one of the weſtern iſles, is the ſpecies of ſeals (as I conjecture) deſcribed by Doctor Parſons, 

                     Ph. Tr. No. 469. and mentioned by M. de Buffon; 
                  Le grand Phoque, xiii. 341.; it reſembles the other in all reſpects but in ſize: a gentleman told me he once killed one near 12 feet long; the common kind ſeldom exceeds ceeds ſix feet.
